cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS, cs.SE 

This paper is focused on evaluating the computational capabilities of neural networks, which is a core topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of automata theory and combinatorial logic, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.SE (Software Engineering).
